#compdef proto-loader-gen-types
# =============================================================================
# proto-loader-gen-types — Google gRPC team's TypeScript-type
#                          generator for .proto files — a
#                          TypeScript-Node CLI that emits TS
#                          interface + type definitions from
#                          Protocol Buffer schemas, designed
#                          to pair with @grpc/proto-loader's
#                          dynamic-loading model (vs static
#                          code-gen).  Distributed as a
#                          binary in @grpc/proto-loader.
#                          Distinguishing from protoc-gen-ts
#                          (third-party), ts-proto, buf
#                          generate (Bufbuild), and other
#                          .proto→TypeScript generators by:
#                            - PAIRED WITH @grpc/proto-loader's
#                              DYNAMIC LOADING — generated
#                              types describe the SHAPE of
#                              protos loaded at runtime via
#                              @grpc/proto-loader's
#                              loadPackageDefinition()
#                              (vs static code-gen where
#                              services + messages are
#                              compiled as JS classes).
#                              proto-loader-gen-types emits
#                              ONLY .ts type files — no
#                              runtime code.
#                            - SEPARATE INPUT + OUTPUT TYPES
#                              — generates BOTH:
#                                * INPUT type (permissive,
#                                  allows partial fields with
#                                  defaults)
#                                * OUTPUT type (restricted,
#                                  exact shape after
#                                  serialization)
#                              via --inputTemplate /
#                              --outputTemplate flag pair (e.g.
#                              `--outputTemplate '%s__Output'`)
#                            - BRANDED TYPES via --inputBranded
#                              / --outputBranded — generated
#                              types include a phantom branding
#                              property carrying the protobuf
#                              fullName, enabling type-safe
#                              discrimination of structurally
#                              identical messages
#                            - 64-BIT INTEGER REPRESENTATION
#                              via --longs={String|Number} —
#                              choose String (for safety —
#                              avoids JS Number precision
#                              loss above 2^53) or Number
#                              (legacy)
#                            - BYTES REPRESENTATION via --bytes
#                              ={Array|String|Buffer} — Buffer
#                              (Node default), Array (browser),
#                              or String (base64)
#                            - ENUMS REPRESENTATION via --enums
#                              =String — emit enums as
#                              string-literal unions instead
#                              of numeric constants
#                            - DEFAULTS via --defaults / --arrays
#                              / --objects — output default
#                              values for omitted fields (so
#                              types reflect runtime
#                              augmentation)
#                            - ONEOF VIRTUAL FIELDS via --oneofs
#                              — emit a virtual field
#                              indicating which oneof case is
#                              present
#                            - COMMENT PRESERVATION via
#                              --includeComments — generated
#                              .ts files include JSDoc
#                              comments from .proto source
#                            - JSON-COMPATIBLE NUMBERS via --json
#                              — Infinity / NaN as strings;
#                              google.protobuf.Any auto-decoded
#                            - --keepCase — preserve original
#                              field names (default is camelCase
#                              transform)
#                            - --grpcLib — specify which gRPC
#                              implementation library the
#                              generated types will be used with
#                              (typically '@grpc/grpc-js'); used
#                              to determine which service-
#                              definition types to emit
#                            - -O / --outDir — output directory
#                              (required)
#                            - -I / --includeDirs — search dirs
#                              for imported .proto files (array)
#                            - --targetFileExtension /
#                              --importFileExtension — control
#                              output file naming (.ts) +
#                              import-specifier extensions for
#                              ESM compatibility
#                          Used by: gRPC Node.js application
#                          developers using @grpc/proto-loader's
#                          dynamic-loading model who want
#                          TypeScript type safety without
#                          static class code-gen, and as the
#                          REFERENCE gRPC-team-authored
#                          TypeScript generator for the
#                          Node.js gRPC ecosystem.
#
# Author:  Google's gRPC team — Michael Lumish (murgatroid99)
#          + Nicolas Noble + grpc-packages npm org.
#          Distributed as `proto-loader-gen-types` binary in
#          the @grpc/proto-loader npm package since 2020.
