# Library: @grpc/grpc-js (https://github.com/grpc/grpc-node —
#          "gRPC Library for Node - pure JS implementation"
#          — Michael Lumish (murgatroid99) + Nicolas Noble +
#          Google gRPC team.  Distinct from tonic (R685, Rust
#          Axis 24 opener) and grpc-go (R686, Go Axis 24
#          expansion) by being:
#             1. PURE JAVASCRIPT IMPLEMENTATION — @grpc/grpc-js
#                is 100% pure JavaScript, implementing gRPC
#                directly over Node's `http2` module.  Distinct
#                from the older `grpc` package (deprecated since
#                2022) which was a Node native addon wrapping
#                grpc-c (C++ core).  Pure-JS enables:
#                  * No Cgo / no native compilation
#                  * Works on Node 16+ universally (no platform
#                    quirks)
#                  * Smaller install size
#                  * Browser-ish environments (with polyfills)
#             2. DUAL CHANNEL OPTIONS — supports both Node's
#                http2 module AND HTTP/1.1 (limited) channel
#                semantics; can emulate "gRPC-Web" for browser-
#                relayed gRPC.
#             3. PROMISIFIED ASYNC API — supports both:
#                  - Callback-style (legacy, gRPC convention)
#                  - Promise-based (modern, async/await)
#                  - Server-streaming via async iterators
#                Same code-gen output works for both API styles.
#             4. METADATA + INTERCEPTORS — Metadata class for
#                key-value pairs; client + server interceptors
#                for cross-cutting concerns (auth, logging,
#                metrics).  Same conceptual model as tonic's
#                interceptor system + grpc-go's Interceptor
#                chains.
#             5. PROTO-LOADER PAIRING via @grpc/proto-loader —
#                dynamic loading of .proto files at runtime
#                (vs static code-gen).  Critical for plug-in
#                architectures + dynamic service discovery.
#                proto-loader-gen-types (THIS) generates the
#                TypeScript types to match.
#             6. SERVER + CLIENT — full gRPC server
#                implementation in pure JS (vs many language
#                ports that are client-only).  Supports SSL/TLS
#                with rotation + mTLS.
#             7. LOAD-BALANCING via pluggable resolvers —
#                round_robin, pick_first; xDS support in
#                progress.  Distinct from grpc-go's mature
#                xDS implementation.
#             8. STREAM CANCELLATION via AbortController —
#                modern Node 16+ AbortController-based
#                cancellation for client streams.
#             9. INTEROPERABLE — passes the gRPC interoperability
#                test suite that all gRPC ports must conform to,
#                ensuring wire-compatibility with tonic + grpc-go
#                + grpc-java + grpc-python + grpc-csharp.
#            10. GOOGLE / grpc-org ECOSYSTEM PROVENANCE — same
#                Google gRPC team maintaining grpc-go (R686).
#                Distinct from Hyperium (tonic, R685 —
#                community-maintained).  Pure-JS implementation
#                is murgatroid99 + Nicolas Noble's primary
